records.addlTxt: COURT ORDERED DEFENDANT REMANDED TO THE COMMISSIONER ON RETURN OF THE BENCH  WARRANT.

Attorney Daniel Mcmurray in court.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for status. DEFENDANT FAILED TO APPEAR. Defense has no explanation for defendants non appearance.
Court ordered bench warrant issued, remand to the Commissioner, and no action on bail.
Justice Point Discharge Report, filed. Forwarded to Judge for review.

Defendant Natasha Brean Harland in court.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Natasha Brean Harland appeared by video means.  Deputy Court Clerk: SD.
Pretrial Conference held.  Public defenders office has not appointed counsel at this time.  Case adjourned, Br. 30.  Status conference scheduled for May 3, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
No use or possession of controlled substances without a valid prescription taken in a manner and fashion as prescribed.
Court orders defendant TO JUSTICE POINT for supervision. Defendant to report to JUSTICE POINT LEVEL 4 immediately upon leaving court. 

IF THE DEFENDANT FAILS TO REPORT A WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.

Defendant Natasha Brean Harland in court.  Ian F Vance-Curzan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 30 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for March 25, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant is Out-of-Custody. Court appearance in Out-Of-Custody Court, Room 221 Safety Building on 3/18/22 @ 1p
